Package: parakeet-ptt
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Saurabh Kadian
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Depends: python3,
         python3-gi,
         python3-gi-cairo,
         gir1.2-gtk-3.0,
         gir1.2-appindicator3-0.1,
         gir1.2-notify-0.7,
         xclip,
         xdotool,
         libportaudio2,
         libsndfile1
Description: Push-to-talk voice dictation powered by NVIDIA Parakeet TDT
 Hold a configurable key to record mic audio. Release to transcribe using
 NVIDIA's Parakeet TDT 0.6B v3 model running fully locally on your GPU.
 Text is pasted directly into the focused window — no API calls, no cloud.
 .
 A system tray app lets you manage the corrections dictionary, change the
 push-to-talk key, and view usage stats. A first-run wizard installs the
 Python virtualenv and downloads the ~2.4 GB model weights.
 .
 Requirements: NVIDIA GPU with 4 GB+ VRAM, NVIDIA driver 520+, X11 session.
